Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho on Wednesday hosted Interior CS Fred Matiang'i during the Eid celebrations in Mombasa. The two enjoyed the local Mombasa beverage 'kahawa' during an Eid Baraza at Treasury Square at the Coastal City. "The Day of Eid-ul-Fitr is a day of great joy and happiness for the Ummah. We are encouraged to enjoy from the Halal bounties that we had refrained from during the month of Ramadan. Such is Allah's Compassion for his servants," Joho later said. Other leaders present at the event wereÂ  Coast regional coordinator John Elungata, Mombasa deputy governor William Kingi, Mvita MP Abdulswamad Nassir among others.